Reasoning: The paper proposes a population-based optimization algorithm that is inspired by philosophical thinking modes and uses dialectic concepts. This algorithm is evaluated on different problems, including single objective continuous functions and compressed sensing. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) for the optimization aspect, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) for the philosophical inspiration and problem-solving approach, cs.LG (Machine Learning) for the use of population-based methods, cs.SY (Systems and Control) for the control aspect of the algorithm, and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) for the evaluation of the algorithm on different problems.
